Create branch from latest remote state of origin master and check it out.

gbnew [branch_name]

	branch_name	Can be copy/pasted from a issue tracker, e.g. JIRA.
			New lines, spaces and other illegal characters 
			will be replaced with a dash (-). 
			First word is left as is the rest are converted
			to lowercase.

E.g. (note the quote marks for multiline argument)

gbnew "JIRA-1234 Fix this and
that"

will create a branch named JIRA-1234-fix-this-and-that
